description:
&lt;p&gt;GP Training Programme Director – Derby&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 session per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GP00 point of national GP educator pay scale&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a permanent opportunity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England East Midlands has responsibility for general practice specialty training and increasingly the multi-professional primary care workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A GP Training Programme Director post is available immediately at the Derby Specialty Training Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be for 1 session a week and the programme is currently based at the Royal Derby Hospital. Please note there will be regular travel around the East Midlands. The programme half day release is currently held on Wednesdays and a Programme Director would be expected to be generally available on a Wednesday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Programme Directors are responsible for managing education in a safe environment for doctors wanting to become GPs. This involves planning, facilitating and evaluating the process of learning. There will be support from the other Programme Directors within the programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this role further, please contact Head of School of Primary Care – Sarah Layzell (Sarah.Layzell@hee.nhs.uk) or Caroline Ahrens (Caroline.Ahrens@hee.nhs.uk)&lt;/p&gt;
